    by martintomazic

    by martintomazic

    go/storage/mkvs/syncer: Add warning about proof size

    by martintomazic

    go/node: Enable configuration of checkpointing algorithm Consensus and runtimes can optionally configure checkpointing algorithm. By default we still use sequential one.

    by martintomazic

    go/worker/storage/committe: Sort checkpoints by peer count P2p network can now have checkpoints from two checkpointing algorithms, each one producing distinct checkpoint for the same root. (In addition to potential byzantine ones...). Observe that underylying checkpoint version is the same, since chunks have the same format, and same restorer can be used. Sorting them by number of peers is desirable since it: 1. decreases overloading early upgraders of the the new chunking algorithm. 2. makes it more reliable for the clients.
